╔════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║           Assignment: permutations             ║
╠════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║ Expected files: *.c, *.h                       ║
║ Allowed functions: puts, malloc, calloc,       ║
║                    realloc, free, write        ║
╚════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

Write a program that will print all the **permutations** of a string given as argument.

The **solutions** must be given in **alphabetical order**.

We will not test your program with strings containing duplicates (e.g., 'abccd').

---

### 💡 Exemplos

$> ./permutations a | cat -e
a$

$> ./permutations ab | cat -e
ab$
ba$

$> ./permutations abc | cat -e
abc$
acb$
bac$
bca$
cab$
cba$